s 21: 13), and as his whole </div><div class="t m8b9 x74 h2d y8bd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">life was given to Christ, his only thought of death </div><div class="t m265 x74 h2d y450 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Was that it might also tend to advance the cause. </div><div class="t m157c xb h2d y606 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">}LESS</div><div class="t m157d x68 h2d y606 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-</div><div class="t m157e x9e h2d y606 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">PO N V. </div><div class="t m638 x47 h34 y988 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MAY 2, 1891. </div><div class="t m8c1 x53 h32 y12e7 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE BLESSED HOPE. PHIL. </div><div class="t m730 x78 h33 y79b ff1 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1:22-3o. </div><div class="t m988 x34 h2d y6d5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m745 x59 h2d y13a9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">WHAT was the one thing that absorbed the </div><div class="t m83f x74 h2d y800 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">apostle Paul&apos;s thoughts? 1 Cur. 2: 2; Phil. 1:18. </div><div class="t m127 x6f h2d y1206 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m42d x59 h2d y801 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Whose honor and glory did he wish promoted ? -</div><div class="t m71a x61 h2d yf72 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Phil. 1 : 20. </div><div class="t m2b6 x6f h2d y4b8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1bc x50 h2d yc40 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What was his sole wish both for his life and </div><div class="t m7c2 x61 h2d yafd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his death? Verses 20, 21; ActS 21 : 13. </div><div class="t ma2 x66 h2d y9db ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m3b8 x50 h2d y96b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How much choice had he, then, between life </div><div class="t m108 x61 h2d y911 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and death ? Phil. 1:22. </div><div class="t m1cd x66 h2d y912 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m157f x50 h2d y23b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III what condition was he? Verse 23, first </div><div class="t m41f x61 h2d yab3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc